And the disciples of John and the Pharisees used to fast; and they came and said to Him, "Why do the disciples of John and the Pharisees fast, but Your disciples do not fast?"
Jesus said to them, "Can the sons of the wedding fast while the bridegroom is with them? As long as the bridegroom is with them, they cannot fast.
But there will come days when the bridegroom is taken away from them; and then they will fast in those days.
No one sews a patch of new cloth on an old garment; otherwise, the new patch will take away from the old, making the tear even worse.
No one puts new wine into old wineskins, or else the new wine will burst the wineskins, the wine will spill out, and the wineskins will be ruined. Instead, they put new wine into new wineskins.
And he went through the grain fields on the Sabbath, and his disciples began to pick the heads of grain while they walked.
And the Pharisees said to him, "Look! Why are they doing what is unlawful on the Sabbath?"
And He said to them, "Have you not read what David did when he was in need and hungry, he and those who were with him?
How did he enter the house of God in the days of Abiathar the high priest, and eat the bread of the presence, which it is not lawful to eat but for the priests, and he gave those who were with him also?
Then he said to them, "The Sabbath was made for man's sake, and not man for the Sabbath's sake.
"If the Son of Man is Lord even of the Sabbath."
Healing on the Sabbath.
Then He also entered the synagogue; and there was a man whose hand was withered.
So they watched him closely to see if he would heal the man on the Sabbath, so that they might accuse him.
And He said to the man who had the withered hand, "Get up in the middle!"
Then he said to them, "Is it lawful on the Sabbath to do good or to do evil? To save a life or to destroy it?" And they were silent.
Looking at them with anger, saddened by their hardness of heart, He said to the man, "Stretch out your hand." And he stretched it out, and his hand was restored, sound like the other.
