Jesus went away with His disciples to the sea; and a great multitude from Galilee and Judea followed Him.
And from Jerusalem and from Edom and from beyond the Jordan. And those around Tyre and Sidon, a great multitude, when they heard how much he had done, they came to him.
And He said to His disciples, "A small ship should keep near Him for the sake of the harvest, so that they do not crowd Him."
For he had often healed many, so that all who had any disease pressed upon him to touch him.
And the unclean spirits, when they saw Him, fell down before Him and cried out, saying, "You are the Son of God!"
And He commanded them greatly not to reveal it. The choosing of the twelve apostles.
Then he went up on the mountain and called those whom he wanted, and they went to him.
And he appointed twelve to be with him and to send them out to preach,
And they shall have power to heal sicknesses and to cast out demons.
And He named Simon Peter.
And James the son of Zebedee, and John the brother of James, and he gave them the name Boanerges, which means Sons of Thunder.
And Andrew, and Philip, and Bartholomew, and Matthew, and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Thaddaeus, and Simon the Canaanite,
And Judas Iscariot, who betrayed him. Then they came to the house. Jesus and Beelzebub
And the crowd gathered again, so that they were not even able to eat bread.
And when His relatives heard about it, they went out to seize Him, for they said, "He is out of His mind!"
As for the scribes who came down from Jerusalem, they said, "He has Beelzebul, and by the prince of demons he casts out demons."
And he called them and spoke to them in parables, saying, "How can a demon cast out a demon?
